/**
 * Two-factor authentication management (admin shell). Two states:
 *   - disabled -> an "Enable" wizard: setup (QR + manual key + recovery codes) then a
 *     live-code confirm (POST /auth/totp-setup, then /auth/totp-activate).
 *   - enabled  -> status + remaining recovery codes + a disable control
 *     (POST /auth/totp-disable, which requires a current code).
 * All mutations are AJAX/JSON — the page never posts to itself.
 *
 * QR rendering is progressive: if a QR renderer (window.QRCode) is present it draws the
 * otpauth URI; otherwise the manual setup key (always shown) is the reliable path —
 * every authenticator app supports "enter a setup key".
 */
